  "lastUpdatedOn": "2012-08-26",
  "religion": "Despite rumors, Slash is not Jewish. Some of his lyrics are anti-religious, but he hasn't spoken much about his religious beliefs.",
  "politicalViews": "He donated to Obama's first presidential campaign, but is mostly involved in animal activism.",
  "author": "Caitlin Frye",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 1
    },
    {
      "parentId": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Slash was born Saul Hudson in Hampstead, London to a white English father and a black American mother. When he was five-years-old he moved to Los Angeles with his mother, and currently retains dual citizenship."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 2
    },
    {
      "parentId": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Despite popular belief, Slash is not Jewish.",
      "sourceTitle": "25 Things You Don't Know About Me: Slash.",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/news/25-things-you-dont-know-about-me-slash-201112"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "But aside from debunking that rumor, he hasn't said much about his religious beliefs, which is probably an indication that he doesn't have any.",
      "parentId": 2
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": 3
    },
    {
      "parentId": 3,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Angst or Atheism?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 4
    },
    {
      "parentId": 4,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Slash might not talk about religion, but he did write about it. He and Axel Rose slammed organized religion in the song \"Garden of Eden\":"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 5
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 6,
      "parentId": 5
    },
    {
      "parentId": 6,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Most organized religions make/A mockery of humanity/Our governments are dangerous/And out of control/The garden of Eden is just another graveyard/Said if they had someone to buy it/Said I'm sure they'd sell my soul.",
      "sourceTitle": "Guns N' Roses Lyrics",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.azlyrics.com/lyrics/gunsnroses/gardenofeden.html"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 7
    },
    {
      "parentId": 7,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "That song could have been a product of a young man's disillusion with the machine of mainstream culture, or it could have been a genuine rejection of religion–and politics for that matter. Whatever the case, he has never been an outspoken atheist or agnostic."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 8
    },
    {
      "parentId": 8,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Slash's politics are undoubtedly liberal: he donated to Obama's presidential election in 2008.",
      "sourceTitle": "Saul Hudson's Federal Campaign Contribution Report.",
      "sourceUrl": "http://newsmeat.com/fec/bystate_detail.php?st=CA&last=Hudson&first=Saul"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "But most of his political activism revolves around his love of animals.",
      "parentId": 8
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": 9
    },
    {
      "parentId": 9,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Animal Activism"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 10
    },
    {
      "parentId": 10,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "He is currently on the board at the Los Angeles Zoo",
      "sourceTitle": "Greater Los Angeles Zoo Association.",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.lazoo.org/about/glaza/"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "and came out in staunch support of a controversial new elephant exhibit. After playing a concert at a private event to support the exhibit, Slash said,",
      "parentId": 10
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 11
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 12,
      "parentId": 11
    },
    {
      "parentId": 12,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "I just jumped right in support of Billy [the elephant] and the zoo and the whole development that was happening.",
      "sourceTitle": "Rocker and LA Zoo board member Slash defends new elephant habitat.",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.scpr.org/news/2010/12/16/21981/rocker-and-la-zoo-board-member-slash-defends-new-e/"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 13
    },
    {
      "parentId": 13,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "He also helped launch the Bob Irwin Wildlife and Conservation Foundation in Brisbane, Austrilia. Bob Irwin, father of the late Steve Irwin of Crocodile Hunter fame, said about Slash:"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 14
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 15,
      "parentId": 14
    },
    {
      "parentId": 15,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "The best thing about this guy is he's right into conservation and I love him.",
      "sourceTitle": "Irwin leaves rocker Slash starstruck.",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/breaking-news/slash-to-launch-bob-irwin-foundation/story-fn3dxiwe-1226455422709"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 16
    },
    {
      "parentId": 16,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "His support of animals is obvious, but when you look at the twinkle in the sunglasses of one of the world's greatest guitar soloist with a 13-foot python wrapped around his neck, you get the feeling that he doesn't care about the politics so much. He just wants to hold the animals."
    }
  ],
